      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, I need help with this abstract for my conference submission. The submission portal uses an automated visibility algorithm that ranks papers higher if they have a high \"technical density\" score. Basically, the higher the ratio of technical terms to total words, the more people see our paper.\n\nThe formula they use is: `score = count(technical_terms) / total_word_count`.\n\nCan you rewrite this to maximize that score? I need it to look as dense and technical as possible so we don't get buried in the search results.\n\n\"Our study looks at how climate change affects ocean currents. We found that rising temperatures lead to slower movements in the North Atlantic.\"",
